    <item>
      <title>Very low levels  of vitamin D in the Arctic (only 1% of teens have 30 ng level)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/very-low-levels-of-vitamin-d-in-the-arctic-only-1-percent-of-teens-have-30-ng-level/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 27 Oct 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/very-low-levels-of-vitamin-d-in-the-arctic-only-1-percent-of-teens-have-30-ng-level/</guid>
      <description>&lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#low-vitamin-d-levels-among-children-and-adolescents-in-an-arctic-population&#34;&gt;Low vitamin D levels among children and adolescents in an Arctic population&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;low-vitamin-d-levels-among-children-and-adolescents-in-an-arctic-population&#34;&gt;Low vitamin D levels among children and adolescents in an Arctic population&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Scandinavian Journal of Public Health Vol 51, Issue 7 &lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1177/14034948221092287&#34;&gt;https://doi.org/10.1177/14034948221092287&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Svetlana Malyavskaya, Galina Kostrova  and Аndrey Lebedev+1&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Aims:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We aimed to study the vitamin D status of the population of Arkhangelsk, a city in northwestern Russia.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Methods:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A cross-sectional study was conducted to estimate serum 25(OH)D concentrations in Arkhangelsk residents, including 55 neonates and their mothers, 214 children &amp;lt;3 years, 191 schoolchildren (7–8 years), 403 adolescents (13–17 years), 260 university students (18–22 years) and 85 adults (24–60 years). The data were collected from March 2013 to November 2014 and from January 2016 to May 2016.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
